title: Summerwater review – back out of the room slowly and carefully … this bleak drama is a mess
summary: The six-part adaptation of Sarah Moss's novel is described as deeply confusing, with melodramatic acting and a bewildering tone. The plot features cartoonishly grim situations that ultimately lack direction. Overall, the series fails to engage effectively with its audience.
